  "text": "Evaluation of a generative model is extremely difficult as it is still not clear how to quantitatively evaluate a generative model. This is due to the difficulty in estimating the intractable log-likelihood in many models [CITATION_1] . The most widely used log-likelihood estimator is the Parzen window estimates [CITATION_2] . However, Theis et al. [CITATION_3] convincingly argued that this estimator can be quite misleading for high-dimensional data. Recently, Salimans et al. [CITATION_4] proposed a different way to assess image quality by using the Inception score (higher is better). The formulation of the Inception score is defined as:",
